    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>chicken</strong> to a clean board and shred it apart using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Add the <strong>shredded chicken</strong>,<strong> cooked onion</strong>, <strong>grated carrot</strong>, <strong>shredded lettuce</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>mint </strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>satay sauce</strong> to the pan with the <strong>drained noodles</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>free range</strong> <strong>chicken satay noodle filling</strong></p>",
